title: Bohemian days;
author: Tadlock, Clara Moyse.
snippet: Here in the Neth-erbow was born the poet Falconer, and the timber-frontedshop and house of the poet Allan Ramsay is a little furtheron. Carubber's Close near by was often visited by Burns,while in Elphinstone and Mint Courts, reached by SouthGray's Close, were fashionable mansions of a few centuriesago where the nobility dwelt and received the lofty in mind aswell as estate. Several are associated with the name of Scott.
